  <body>
   <p>"Orphan asylums have almost everything else but orphans in them these days", declares the Children's Dureau of the Department of Labor after completing a survey of these institutions.</p>
   <p>Information gathered from nine states shows that out of a total of nearly twenty thousand children, wholly or partially dependent on public aid, only five percent were real orphans, while sixty percent five percent had both parents living.</p>
   <p>Investigation showed that separation and divorce were by far the greatest menace to the welfare of minors.</p>
